g.text: When enabled and using OpenHands LLM provider, an experimental critic
model predicts task success likelihood in real-time. The score is
displayed after each agent action. We collect anonymized data (IDs, critic
response, feedback) to evaluate accuracy. See:
When enabled, if the critic predicts a low success probability OR detects
a specific issue (e.g., insufficient testing) above the issue threshold, a
follow-up message is automatically sent to the agent asking it to review
The overall critic score threshold (1-100%) below which iterative
refinement is triggered. Default: 60%. Lower values mean refinement only
